            "summary": "Stirling Mk.III BK770 arrived with 75(NZ) Squadron on 2 April 1943 and was lost on 8 April during an operation to Duisburg. A brief W/T distress signal was received at 01:10hrs before the aircraft crashed at Valley Farm, Bressingham, Norfolk, exploding on impact. This was the first Mk III Stirling written off by 75(NZ) Squadron.",
